@obxjuggler, I think what you are looking for is called a parallax.
To do this you would create a  or  in your html, then assign that class (.parallax in css) a background-image.  Set the background-image to:
/* Parallax Section */
.parallax {
	background-color: #4181C3;
	background-image: url(PARALLAX-wave.png);
	height: 400px;
	background-attachment: fixed;
	background-size: cover;
	background-repeat: no-repeat;
	background-position: center center;
}

I think the key you are looking for is ‘background-attachment: fixed;’
Keep in mind it’s important to set a background color, because the parallax feature does not work on mobile devices.  If you still want the image to appear on mobile devices, you can set a @media query, and just remove the ‘fixed’.
